observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a) Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Officer (MENRO) to intensify the information, education, communication and advocacy campaign program of the Municipality, specially on the Solid Waste segregation, reduction, re-use and recycling of waste; 
b) Municipal Engineer to expedite the construction of the Sanitary Landfill Facility with MRF in Barangay Sajud-Ulan: Sanitary Landfill in which is the phase the electrification which will be completed on February 21, 2021; 
c) MENRO and Municipal Engineer to facilitate the repair of shredder machine in the Public Market so that the existing MRF would be operational; 
d) MENRO to adopt a system of monitoring its waste diversion target congruent through submission to the Municipality’s Solid Waste Management Plan; and Barangay MRS Report of all barangays; and 
e) concerned officials to provide the necessary support in establishing functional MRF to other Barangays and strictly implement the no segregation/no collection policy and comply with all other prescribed procedures and guidelines under RA No. 9003 to avoid additional cost for collection, hauling and disposal of garbage.
